OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMaths pupil stripped of    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25FGCSE amid cheating claim   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A pupil was stripped of his maths GCSE 
OL,6, after a question he found online while 
OL,7, revising appeared on his exam paper.   
OL,9,FEmil Bednarski, 17, who studies at     
OL,10,FKensington Aldridge Academy, had asked 
OL,11,Fa teacher for help with the question   
OL,12,Fjust before sitting the exam.          
OL,14,FThe school reported it to exam board   
OL,15,FPearson, who refused to issue his GCSE.
OL,16,FOn appeal, he was awarded his GCSE but 
OL,17,Fa Grade 5, as one paper was discounted.
OL,19,FEmil said he had "no need to cheat at  
OL,20,Fmaths" and plans to resit next month.  
